SUMMARY:Ão
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Warm-blooded & ethereal electronic pop\n\nBelgian formation Ão
 ’s debut album ‘Ao Mar’ is Portuguese for ‘to the sea’.It’s ha
 rd to imagine a more apt way to describe their enchanting\, constantly unf
 urling music. Ão’s songs are texturally rich odysseys where electronic 
 music\, dream pop\, saudade\, ambient folk and neojazz constantly shape-sh
 ift: habitually in the most surprising\, emotionally resonant ways.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-028642517893d705@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T141500Z
DTEND:20260611T150000Z
SUMMARY:Leoniden
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Meteoric indie-punk anthems\n\nSentimentality becomes the most 
 epic of quests with German indie-punk outfit Leoniden: anthems crammed wit
 h pure-hearted\, euphoric adrenaline. Such punching-the-air fanfare needs 
 an equally powerful foil\, which arrives in the shape of disarmingly frank
 \, unpolished lyricism\, bringing a depth and nuance that underpins the gr
 oup's hard-hitting sound. Leoniden is a no-holds-barred\, no-compromise\, 
 leaving-it-all-on-the-floor operation\, and we can never have enough bands
  like this.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-54d81d399c223aae@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T160000Z
DTEND:20260611T170000Z
SUMMARY:MAVI
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Rap spirituals of a different caliber\n\nMavi has become a gene
 rational voice of hip-hop's blossoming underground.\nIn both style and sub
 stance\, the Charlotte-born rapper has truly proven himself in a league of
  his own: impressionistic\, ambitious\, experimental and community driven.
  It has put two modern classics\, Laughing so Hard\, it Hurts (2022) and i
 ts mirage-like follow-up\, shadowbox (2024)\, on the map. Indeed\, the sky
  is in Mavi’s future… and the very limit of what he can achieve.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d6c42a16a7d025c8@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T180000Z
DTEND:20260611T190000Z
SUMMARY:Model/Actriz
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:New York-based industrial-glam powerhouse\n\nSwans\, Sonic Yout
 h\, the whole no wave movement – New York has always been fertile ground
  for loud music\, and Model/Actriz are enjoying the buffet.This band bring
 s a different type of flair to the fore: have you ever imagined Gomez Adda
 ms fronting Nine Inch Nails\, or Marc Almond featuring on a Gilla Band alb
 um? The mix of deafening noise and vaudevillian charm make Model/Actriz im
 possible to resist: their shows trigger a fundamental need for pure cathar
 sis.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f11d9c6963ed9b66@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T200000Z
DTEND:20260611T210000Z
SUMMARY:Ata Kak
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Infectious Afrobeats cult hero\n\nAta Kak’s rise as cult phen
 omenon shows us the power of Doing It Yourself – how it can cultivate so
 me completely original pop music. Yaw Atta-Owusu knew he liked reggae musi
 c\, he liked funk\, he liked Ghanaian high life music\, and he liked Grand
 master Flash. But why pick just one? With the necessary recording equipmen
 t\, his signature Twi flow and an unblemished zest for life\, Ata Kak’s 
 legendary LP Obaa Sima became a global grassroots success. And we're still
  dancing feverishly to its tunes today.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-6bb7be3751748e63@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T214500Z
DTEND:20260611T224500Z
SUMMARY:MEROL
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Dutch pop's Most Entertaining Role Model\n\nAs the pre-eminent 
 risk taker within the Dutch mainstream\, you can always count on MEROL fea
 rlessly plunge into the deepest end.The imagery of a shark – the creatur
 e she depicts on latest LP Naar De Haaien & Weer Terug – makes a lot of 
 sense: MEROL can breach the surface with razor-sharp\, risque EDM bangers\
 , but also express the introspective struggle below with layered pop gems.
  Both on stage and on her records\, fun\, danger and vulnerability are MER
 OL's favorite bedfellows.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-21f529d447074ad0@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T230000Z
DTEND:20260612T003000Z
SUMMARY:Indie Gloria
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Indie gems served by the barrel\n\nIndie Gloria is that heartfe
 lt embrace with your friends when you are surprised by a brilliant track.\
 nThis Hague-based duo\, consisting of Wouter Andeweg and Abel Vlaanderen\,
  shares a love for innovative dance\, indie\, and pop. Together\, they del
 iver an energetic set where they effortlessly play Four Tet\, Fontaines D.
 C.\, and Charli XCX in one breath.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-574d95cd8609e39c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T110000Z
DTEND:20260612T114500Z
SUMMARY:Madra Salach
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Enchanting electronica-tinged folk\n\nDublin sextet Madra Salac
 h write gripping electronica-infused folk\, scrambling tradition with rein
 vention in baffling ways.\nOriginally playing in various groups\, their sh
 ared love of the Irish traditional canon led to a spontaneous band playing
  in pubs. Inspired by the growing Irish experimental folk scene\, Madra Sa
 lach’s songs\, while thematically modern\, are written with a voice that
  could have originated at any point in the last century.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-27116e206ab5a9a2@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T123000Z
DTEND:20260612T131500Z
SUMMARY:Maddie Ashman
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Eerie and beautiful\, Maddie Ashman's music sounds like folk so
 ngs gone through the digital wood chipper\, glued together like a strange 
 collage.\nThe UK composer\, performer\, and songwriterr often explores the
  connections between sound and the environment. As a result\, her music fe
 els emblematic to the desire to escape technology’s clutches\, and the y
 earning for something more human and imperfect.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-73eca1b99f7cacde@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T140000Z
DTEND:20260612T144500Z
SUMMARY:Sorry
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Indie rock with a novelistic bite\n\nSorry imbue their cinemati
 c & angular indie rock with the storytelling prowess of a distinguished no
 velist.Seedy tales of the city\, the taboos of love and sex\, the horrors 
 of post-modern living – Asha Lorenz and Louis O’ Bryen intend to unpac
 k it all. The band’s fantastic latest LP Cosplay unmasks both their inne
 r tensions and the pretenses of the outside world.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ec19a8abee4a3583@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T154500Z
DTEND:20260612T163000Z
SUMMARY:Radio Free Alice
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Hazy post-punk and new wave risers\n\nWith their layered atmosp
 heric songs\, Aussie new wave/post-punk group Radio Free Alice sound nosta
 lgic and fresh at once.\nThere’s a misty\, dream-like quality to the ban
 d\, inviting that deja vu feeling that you heard their songs before\, long
  ago. We hear the honed song craft of The Smiths and Orange Juice\, combin
 ed with the dark brooding atmospherics of a Joy Division and Interpol. Ind
 eed\, Radio Free Alice have all the elements of a band to cherish for deca
 des to come.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-c4766740825ebbf4@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T173000Z
DTEND:20260612T183000Z
SUMMARY:Tropical Fuck Storm
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Noisy blues punk abomination\n\nImagine all of your favorite ro
 ck bands melted down into some sort of stenchy primordial soup\, only to r
 ise and reform.\nThat\, in a nutshell\, is would be Tropical Fuck Storm. S
 ince the year 2017\, these rock veterans have torn up the rulebook of what
  constitutes as guitar music in the most mind-blowing ways. Through sickne
 ss\, strife\, and squalls of noise – Tropical Fuck Storm is as resilient
  to apocalyptic occurences as the famous cockroach.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-835624707ec3a587@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T193000Z
DTEND:20260612T203000Z
SUMMARY:The Zawose Queens
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Rapturous Gogo spirituals\n\nTanzania's Zawose Queens channel v
 ibrations of the ancestors through their rapturous polyphonic singing. As 
 the daughter and granddaughter of the legendary Dr. Hukwe Zawose\, Leah an
 d Pendo are ushering in the family tradition as its first female practitio
 ners. Their fusion of the Gogo music and modern-day electronics expresses 
 a deep connection towards nature\, to ceremony and to ritual: music teemin
 g with unshakable spirit and fire.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e7eac73ddcc2363e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T213000Z
DTEND:20260612T223000Z
SUMMARY:BCUC
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Fast & furious Afro-psych jams\n\nThe Afropsychedelic pounce of
  Bantu Continua Uhuru Consciousness screams with a zealous\, ceremonial sp
 irit.BCUC's formula seems so simple when you break it down: bass\, drums\,
  percussion\, voice chants all conspiring to spark frantic\, joyous moveme
 nt. And the Soweto\, South-Africa based collective does this better than a
 nyone: this is music awakened from ancient lineage\, yet visionary\, loud 
 and transcending convention of what a band can be.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-434965af5930716d@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T233000Z
DTEND:20260613T020000Z
SUMMARY:Lucky Done Gone
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Genre-blending DJ who brings that rare dancefloor euphoria\n\nI
 f one is forced to narrow down a Lucky Done Gone DJ set in just two terms\
 , it would be ‘carefree and contagious’.\nAnd if a third signifier can
  be cheated in\, you can add 'genre-blurring' to the mix as well. Like a m
 agpie who loves all shiny things\, Lucky cherrypicks his favorite elements
  from basically any imaginable club movement – be it house\, 90s techno\
 , 00s trance\, old school or new school – and mold it into something fre
 sh and euphoria-inducing. A master at his craft\, passion and proficiency 
 personified.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9040766e8ddad86a@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T104500Z
DTEND:20260613T113000Z
SUMMARY:Dressed Like Boys
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Intimate & resonant pop phenomenon\n\nDressed Like Boys\, the s
 olo project of artist Jelle Denturck\, is both intrusively intimate and st
 unningly grandiose.The Ghent-based songwriter tackles his experiences as a
  gay man from personal history\, as well as the history of humankind\, wit
 hin a framework of timeless pop staples like The Beatles\, David Bowie\, S
 ufjan Stevens and Elton John. Though Denturck’s songs are often rooted i
 n hardship and struggle\, they always breach the soil with uncanny emotion
 al power and spirited flair – his self-titled debut staking its place as
  a modern classic of Belgian pop.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-279dbcbd1ea2c4ee@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T121500Z
DTEND:20260613T130000Z
SUMMARY:Mên An Tol
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Fresh-faced folk-inspired guitar anthems\n\nMên An Tol are nam
 ed after an ancient rock formation in their native Cornish\, which may tel
 l you something about their overall approach to rock music.\nIn this high 
 velocity society\, you see an increasing number of bands harken back to th
 e communal\, nostalgic spirit of folk. Mên An Tol are fresh faces in this
  scene\, already obtaining big fans in Fontaines DC and The Libertines wit
 h their bittersweet & timeless anthems – the kind of music that’ll tan
 talise fans of The Waterboys\, The Pogues and R.E.M..
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-27257f8d0f947adb@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T134500Z
DTEND:20260613T143000Z
SUMMARY:Skullcrusher
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Spectral folk of quiet devastation\n\nQuietude can be extremely
  heavy\, something Skullcrusher’s hazy alt-folk most certainly illustrat
 es.\nFunny thing: the Skullcrusher moniker was hatched by Helen Ballentine
  when she started a DJ project mixing My Bloody Valentine and Autechre. Wh
 en that didn't pan out\, it just stuck when she decided to pen haunting fi
 nger-picking folk songs that seem to exist inside of a David Lynch or Kiyo
 shi Kurasawa picture. Skullcrusher expertly treads a fine line between bea
 uty and devastation.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ebfb43a2b0d61e8a@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T153000Z
DTEND:20260613T163000Z
SUMMARY:Getdown Services
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Jolly have-a-go 'power disco' hijinks\n\nThe ‘plan’ behind 
 Getdown Services was to have no plan at all: except basking in some fearle
 ss fumbling about and fun.\nThis sense of abandon morphs into a thrifty mi
 x of eighties pop\, post-punk\, and classic rock that’s frequently been 
 dubbed as ‘power disco’. Indeed\, these two freewheeling Bristolians s
 eem to make it up as they go along\, and it often unfolds in similar comed
 ic brilliance as in that famous sitcom “Peep Show”. A love for all thi
 ngs music-related\, from Chic to AC/DC\, is worn on Getdown Services' furr
 owed sleeves.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-878117e0528ceb83@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T173000Z
DTEND:20260613T183000Z
SUMMARY:Genesis Owusu
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Bombshell blender of rap\, post-punk & indie\n\nOne of his LPs 
 might be called Struggler\, the way Ghanaian/Australian artist Genesis Owu
 su mixes styles like post-punk\, rap\, pop\, funk and electro feels downri
 ght effortless.\nA Bloc Party riff here\, a lo-fi beat there\, a string se
 ction out of nowhere – Owusu's songs forge unity by means of the most in
 explicable of spare parts. His singular creativity as a producer is matche
 d by his subversive sharp-witted wordplay. Lawless\, formless\, thoughtles
 s\, flawless!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-75f9b9fcbc324cee@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T193000Z
DTEND:20260613T203000Z
SUMMARY:Gelli Haha
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Wacky\, wonky cartoon pop\n\nGelli Haha pens magnetic and kalei
 doscopic synth pop/electroclash tunes that seem to tumble straight out of 
 a Dr. Seuss-novel.\nThe music of the Los Angeles-based artist is merely th
 e starting point: the self-coined Gelliverse paints all surroundings into 
 a multi-coloured big top spectacle one can not help but be immersed in. Th
 e perfect live experience for unleashing your inner infant.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9f029c84c82e4370@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T214500Z
DTEND:20260613T223000Z
SUMMARY:Parker Fans
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Mischief-making indie boogie trio\n\nThere’s a fuzzy sentimen
 t to Parker Fans’ self-described ‘three-way boogie bromance’\, shuff
 ling styles with a magpie’s spirit.Gabber house flirtations\, hip-hop ho
 edowns\, breakbeat bonanzas: this Dutch trio has a knack for courting all 
 kinds of unexpected chaos – often of the gleeful variety. Fully aware of
  the futility of having too much fun\, Parker Fans are squiggly\, scatterb
 rained and compulsively scene-causing.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
